    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-08-15T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-08-15T13:00:00-05:00" n="684"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d684">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.613/8–850: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Soviet Union</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-08-15T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 15, 1950—2 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>131. ReEmbtel 348 Aug 8.<note n="1" xml:id="d684fn1">The Embassy had asked for
                        reconsideration in this telegram, not printed, for the part-time employment
                        of Father Brassard because of the prevailing circumstances in his position
                        and because he would be a valuable asset to the Embassy staff. He had sought
                        employment since time was “heavy on his hands” and he had not believed that
                        his superiors would find this objectionable. The Embassy declared that it
                        would “continue to maintain in future in dealings with Soviet Government
                        concerning Father Brassard’s performance of his religious functions that he
                        has no connection with US Government or Embassy.” (124.613/8–850)</note>
                    Careful consideration given <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>’s renewed
                    request auth employ Father Brassard. Despite factors mentioned by <gloss
                        target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>, Dept on basis over-all implications of such
                    step unable agree auth employment.</p>
                <pb facs="1249" n="1233" xml:id="pg_1233"/>
                <p>Father Brassard’s principals called on Dept officers Aug 9 and in course gen
                    conversation stated Father Brassard had mentioned in recent ltr possibility
                        <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> employment. According to them ltr had
                    already been sent cautioning him against such step.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
